This problem is variation of **2 sum**  poblem where we need to find the pairs equivalent to the given target.
The 2 sum problem is further extended to **3 sum** where we need to return the tripet of array which is equal to 0.
How this problem 3 sum closest is extension of 3 sum : 
here we just need to find three integers of nums vector that has closest sum to the given target.**

**Steps to find closest 3 sum to the given target:**
1) sort the array(through sorting we can increase the efficiency of the solution)
   unless and until the array is sorted applying two pointer doesn't make sense.
2)  use two pointer approach 
3)  make a left pointing next to i and a right pointer at the end of it
4)  make a curr_sum variable 
5)  check for the condition if target - curr_sum < min_diff
6)  if curr_sum > target than decrement the right pointer 
7)  else increment left pointer.
 **Time complexity - O(N^2)** 
 **space complexity - O(1)** as no extra space required

```
class Solution {
public:
    int threeSumClosest(vector<int>& nums, int target) {
        sort(nums.begin(), nums.end());

        int min_difference = INT_MAX;
        int result =0;
        for(int i =0; i< nums.size() ; i++){
           int left = i +1; 
            int right = nums.size()-1;

            while(left < right){

                int curr_sum = nums[i] + nums[left]+ nums[right];
                if(abs(target - curr_sum) < min_difference ){
                      min_difference = abs(target - curr_sum);
                      result = curr_sum;
                }
                if( curr_sum > target) right--;
                else{
                    left++;
                }
               if(target == curr_sum) return result;
            }
        }
        return result;
    }

};
